在TypeScript中，可以使用“any”类型来告诉类型系统“理论上，这个值可能有多种类型，但实际上我知道它只会有这一种类型”。 Here is an example of how to do this:
```typescript
const value = 42;

function doSomething(value: any): void {
  // value is of type any, which means it could be any type, but I know it's really a number.
  // You can do anything you want with it, because it's guaranteed to be a number.
}
```
Note that this only works if you know for sure that the value will only have one specific type. If you are not sure about the type, you should use the "unknown" type instead.

